beer.beer_description: Cheers to good neighbours! This Japanese inspired rice lager was brewed with our good buds from Bracket to celebrate the opening of their new brewery around the corner. Summer is looking Golden!
A classic American Pale Ale hopped with Chinook, Cascade, Strata and Rakau for pine, citrus, berry and stone fruit.
A celebration of Indie Hops from Oregon, the latest rendition of our house hazy pale showcases Strata alongside relative newcomer Luminosa.

The brewer's sleight of hand is at play here, deftly selecting hops to conjure up a delectable nectar that's greater than the sum of its parts!
Tropical notes in abundance on the nose and palate with citrus, passionfruit and the classic Nelson sav blanc wine notes. A soft pillowy mouthfeel with a restrained bitterness and a subtle bready malt backdrop that allows the hops to truly shine.

A hazy IPA showcasing the finest New Zealand hops. Dry hopped with Waimea, Motueka and Cascade.
The first beer in our series focussing on the splendour of New Zealand hops. Loaded with Waimea, Motueka and Cascade hops from Freestyle Hops in Nelson, this beer is layered with bright orange and lime, creamy tropical and subtle berry notes, with Waimea adding a little spice with its signature spruce pine undertones. A super soft mouthfeel and subtle sweetness from the oat & wheat heavy grain bill play off the gentle bitterness and keep you coming back for another sip. We hope this beer opens people's eyes to some of the new and exciting flavours that they can experience with New Zealand hops.
For this 1st Birthday release we teamed up with our pals at Bracket to brew a DDH Hazy IPA. No surprises for guessing that Motueka features in a big way!

Our biggest, boldest, baddest hazy IPA to date? We won't get carried away with hyperbole here. Instead we'll let the powerhouse combo of Strata, Nelson and Motueka do all the talking and you can decide for yourself!
This GABS special release showcases southern hemisphere hops Vic Secret, Galaxy and Wakatu!

A dry and bitter California IPA indulgently hopped with Strata, Mosaic and Simcoe hops.

A lean, clean, crushable California IPA might feel like an imposter in this post modern landscape of soft, hazy, juicy IPAs but this couldn't be further from the truth! Imposter Syndrome is a dry and bitter IPA, inspired by its West Coast IPA forebears, but with a pared back malt bill to let the hops take centre stage. Indie Hops' brainchild Strata leads the way with passionfruit, melon and its trademark resinous, cannabis notes. It gets support from good friends Mosaic and Simcoe adding some tropical complexity and citrus undertones. This beer is the perfect companion as we enter the warmer months and dangerously drinkable, even at 7.3%!

Seeking inspiration in the mountain of hops in the cool room there came a whisper. Motueka, Motueka, Motueka! In a beer that we hope will make Mike from Bracket smile, we threw pellets from 2 lots of Mot and the experimental Kohia Motueka hop kief at this juicy boy!
This GABS special release showcases two of the biggest hops out there, Galaxy and Citra!

Putting the spotlight on Freestyle Hops' Riwaka in all its glory. Expect exotic citrus, papaya and candy flavours to jump out of the glass. Backed up with a more modest dose of our house favourite, Nelson Sauvin, with its dank passion fruit and guava flavour profile.
This 'Juicy' special Hazy IPA is boasting huge green citrus & pineapple notes and is straight up ripe for the picking.

beer.beer_description:
For our biggest hazy to date we set out to prove the synergistic effect of combining Southern Cross hops with perennial fave Nelson Sauvin. Let's just say it pops!

Hops: Freestyle Hops Southern Cross, Nelson Sauvin & Maui Nelson Hop Kief,
Eggers Hops Nelson Sauvin

A super hoppy hazy pale ale jam-packed with Motueka, Citra and Idaho 7 hops.
Towards the Light is the kind of pale ale we love to drink. It gets hit with a heavy dose of Motueka with just enough Citra and Idaho 7 to round things out. Expect punchy lime zest, bright tropical peachy notes and a little bit of pungent weedy pine that Idaho is renowned for in the background. A light malt base with an abundance of raw wheat and malted oats brings the soft juicy mouthfeel that you're looking for with just enough sweetness to tie it all together. This is one pale ale that ain't gonna sit in the shadows of its bigger IPA brothers!
This birthday special is a naked expression of hops in the best way possible. Using a super light grain bill and fermented with a lager yeast this beer puts the the hops front and centre!

beer.beer_description: This big ol' juicy DDH DIPA is our first release to feature the heavy hitting NZ hop combo of Nelson Sauvin and Motueka from 2 of our favourite indie NZ hop farms. You know this is going to be good!

With berries, cherries, lime, peach and more this hazy IPA is brimming with the good stuff.

Hops: HBC630, Motueka and Mosaic
Our house style west coast IPA. Bone dry, moderately bitter and super hoppy with a mix of pine, tropical and citrus flavours.

For this 'Juicy' special edition of Double Nelson we pushed the boundaries further with the inclusion of Freestyle Hops experimental Kohia Nelson Hop Kief in addition to 2 lots of traditional T90 pellets!

beer.beer_description: The next iteration of our house hazy pale is sunshine in a glass. Cheers to the warmer weather that’s just around the corner!
Oozing with decadent chocolate and coconut macaroon flavours this unctuous imperial dessert stout is the perfect companion for sitting by the record player on a dark winter's night.

Gaze into the future of flavour with this Thiolised Hazy IPA. Loaded with Phantasm, heavily mash hopped and using a thiol producing yeast strain, this beer showcases a huge tropical flavour profile with only a fraction of our usual dry hop load. The future is now!
Our first foray into barrel ageing, this decadent imperial stout aged in whisky barrels is rich and full bodied with jammy fruit and spice, and a lingering creamy sweetness.
